[It will be interesting to compare UK surveillance data with those
available on the Danish and German national websites (see
20060412.1085). Unfortunately, the data of the UK surveillance in
wild birds could not be traced on the DEFRA or VLA websites. If this
moderator has missed available data, he will be glad to stand
corrected. - Mod.AS]
[One must emphasize that migratory birds are just one of the routes
by which H5N1 travels. Commercial poultry traveling whole or in part
are still held to be a higher economic risk. - Mod.MHJ]
